Business Brief -- Bank of Boston Corp.:
   First National Bank Unit
   Acquires Certain Deposits
New Heritage Bank had total assets of about $89.9 million,
the FDIC said. Deposits totaled about $90.8 million in about
1,600 deposit accounts, including about $1.2 million in 47
accounts that exceeded the federal insurance limit of
$100,000.
   The FDIC said First National Bank of Boston will purchase
certain assets of the failed bank for $19.2 million. The
agency added that it will retain assets of New Heritage Bank
with a book value of $75.4 million.